Group A: Short Questions (2 Marks)
1. Define the term ”Sitemap” in the planning phase.
Sitemap (Planning Phase):
A sitemap is a structured outline or diagram that shows the organization of all pages of a website and how they are linked together, 
used during the planning phase to design clear navigation and site structure.
2. What is the purpose of the ”Launch” phase in web development?
Purpose of the Launch Phase:
The launch phase in web development involves making the website live and accessible to users on the Internet. 
It ensures that all features work correctly, the site is uploaded to the web server, 
and any final testing, security checks, and optimizations are completed before public access.
3. Why is ”Documentation” important in the development lifecycle?
Documentation is important because it records all details of the website or software, including design, code, features, and functionality. 
It helps developers, testers, and future maintainers to understand, update, and troubleshoot the system efficiently. 
It also ensures consistency, clarity, and knowledge transfer throughout the development lifecycle.
